      {
        "type": "email",
        "html": "<p>Hello, {first_name, \"there\"},</p><p>Welcome to a lunchtime delivery of critical reading around the intersection of digital journalism and social media. You're getting this newsletter because you registered at <em>One Man &amp; His Blog</em> - but you can unsubscribe with a single click at the bottom.&nbsp;</p>"
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalrule"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "It's been quite a few days since I last wrote one of these. And they have been startling ones, even in these strange times. In the UK, the power of the media to change public opinion has been reasserted in dramatic form, as reports of the Prime Minister's closest aide's behaviour during lockdown broke out of the media bubble, and spread across the whole country. A ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Daily Mail",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " poll showed that ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "the vast majority of the country think he",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "https://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-8359511/Majority-Conservative-supporters-believe-Dominic-Cummings-sacked.html",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " should go.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "There is ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "so much ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "to unpick in this, but I'm not going to have time to do so until next week. And who knows where things will be by then?",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Twitter versus Trump",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "heading",
        "tag": "h2",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "However, that's not the only change in the landscape. Twitter has finally started developing a backbone about the misinformer-in-chief:",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "bookmark",
        "url": "https://www.vox.com/recode/2020/5/26/21271210/twitter-fact-check-trump-tweets-mail-voting-fraud-rigged-election-misleading-statements",
        "metadata": {
          "url": "https://www.vox.com/recode/2020/5/26/21271210/twitter-fact-check-trump-tweets-mail-voting-fraud-rigged-election-misleading-statements",
          "title": "Twitter has finally started fact-checking Trump",
          "description": "For the first time, Twitter took action against Trump’s misleading tweets.",
          "author": "Shirin Ghaffary",
          "publisher": "Vox",
          "thumbnail": "https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/SM0rJolBtZv09CeRHV7QNVGsArE=/0x414:3096x2035/fit-in/1200x630/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/20003913/1227244978.jpg.jpg",
          "icon": "https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/6397051/recode_favicon-192.0.png"
        }
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "This is a significant move, because now it's stepped over this line, the company has to decide when it will do so in future, and in as consistent a manner as it can. Twitter has been one of the major vectors for the President to spread misinformation. Trying to cram the horse back into the stable and close the door is going to be a sisyphean task, if you'll excuse the mixed metaphor. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "For example, this decision is not playing out well:",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "bookmark",
        "url": "https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-52810661",
        "metadata": {
          "url": "https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-52810661",
          "title": "Twitter will not remove Trump’s ‘horrifying lies’",
          "description": "The company says it is “deeply sorry” for the pain caused by the tweets about a woman’s 2001 death.",
          "author": "BBC News",
          "publisher": "BBC News",
          "thumbnail": "https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/1024/branded_news/11F6D/production/_112518537_tv061489786.jpg",
          "icon": "https://static.bbc.co.uk/news/1.315.03594/apple-touch-icon.png"
        }
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "In that context this is an interesting interview: ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "bookmark",
        "url": "https://reutersinstitute.politics.ox.ac.uk/risj-review/i-think-removing-content-donald-trump-will-always-have-meet-very-high-bar",
        "metadata": {
          "url": "https://reutersinstitute.politics.ox.ac.uk/risj-review/i-think-removing-content-donald-trump-will-always-have-meet-very-high-bar",
          "title": "“I think removing content by Donald Trump will always have to meet a very high bar”",
          "description": "Richard Allan has spent most of his life working on issues related with politics and tech. He left Facebook at the end of 2019 after 10 years in various public policy roles. Before joining the company, he was a member of the UK Parliament for eight years and he was appointed to the House of Lords in…",
          "author": "Eduardo Suárez Tuesday 19 May 2020",
          "publisher": "Reuters Institute for the Study of Journalism",
          "thumbnail": "https://reutersinstitute.politics.ox.ac.uk/sites/default/files/styles/feature_box/public/2020-05/key_richard-allan.png.jpeg?itok=uw_Bm7lv",
          "icon": "https://reutersinstitute.politics.ox.ac.uk/themes/custom/reuters/favicon.ico"
        }
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Oh, Facebook",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "heading",
        "tag": "h3",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Of course, Facebook knew that it was causing division to grow in society years ago. And what did it do?",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "It shrugged:",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "bookmark",
        "url": "https://www.wsj.com/articles/facebook-knows-it-encourages-division-top-executives-nixed-solutions-11590507499",
        "metadata": {
          "url": "https://www.wsj.com/articles/facebook-knows-it-encourages-division-top-executives-nixed-solutions-11590507499",
          "title": "Facebook Executives Shut Down Efforts to Make the Site Less Divisive",
          "description": "The social-media giant internally studied how it polarizes users, then largely shelved the research",
          "author": "Jeff Horwitz and Deepa Seetharaman",
          "publisher": "The Wall Street Journal",
          "thumbnail": "https://si.wsj.net/public/resources/images/B3-GT627_POLARI_SOC_20200525195739.jpg",
          "icon": "https://s.wsj.net/media/wsj_apple-touch-icon-180x180.png"
        }
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "This should be shocking at a basic human level, let alone a corporate responsibility one. But we've all come to expect this from them, haven't we?",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The Subscriptions Boom",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "heading",
        "tag": "h2",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "I'm not going to surprise anyone here by saying that this has been a rough couple of months for media businesses. The super short version is that there are three major streams of revenue for media companies right now:",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "Ads",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "listitem",
            "value": 1,
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "Events",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "listitem",
            "value": 2,
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "Subscriptions",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "listitem",
            "value": 3,
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "tag": "ul",
        "type": "list",
        "listType": "bullet",
        "start": 1,
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The pandemic has brutalised two of those for the time being - and so, attention has shifted to the third: subscriptions. For some, the news has been good.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "bookmark",
        "url": "https://digiday.com/media/so-far-publishers-are-keeping-subscribers-gained-during-the-coronavirus-crisis/",
        "metadata": {
          "url": "https://digiday.com/media/so-far-publishers-are-keeping-subscribers-gained-during-the-coronavirus-crisis/",
          "title": "So far, publishers are keeping subscribers gained during the coronavirus crisis - Digiday",
          "description": "People subscribing during coronavirus are less likely to churn.",
          "author": "Lucinda Southern",
          "publisher": "Digiday",
          "thumbnail": "https://digiday.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/retention.jpg",
          "icon": "https://digiday.com/wp-content/themes/digiday/static/images/favicons/favicon-196x196.png"
        }
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "There's a lot more information on the subject in the INMA report by Grzegorz Piechota, which I was lucky enough to edit. It's a fascinating read, that explores in detail exactly which readers are becoming subscribers - and how you might go about retaning them.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Highly recommended (but I would say that, wouldn't I?):",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "bookmark",
        "url": "https://www.inma.org/report-detail.cfm?pubid=207",
        "metadata": {
          "url": "https://www.inma.org/report-detail.cfm?pubid=207",
          "title": "INMA: Report - News Subscriptions In the Age of Coronavirus",
          "description": "INMA is the world’s leading provider of global best practices and marketing ideas for newsmedia companies, and provides members with information on newspaper industry trends, growing an audience, advertising, and profits.",
          "author": null,
          "publisher": "News Subscriptions In the Age of Coronavirus",
          "thumbnail": "https://www.inma.org/img/inma-logo.png",
          "icon": "https://www.inma.org/favicon.ico"
        }
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "More to come on that subject, but again, probably not until next week. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
